<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,310,1374,1400]" box="[189,310,1374,1400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1374,1400]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1374,1400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[188,1399,1421,1553]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
The salient features of this new species include: left side of ventral margin of periandrium with a beltshaped process in apical third (
<figureCitation box="[549,641,1456,1482]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
); dorsal margin of endosoma with multiple small teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1382,1456,1482]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
); basal left side of endosoma with a long spinose process (
<figureCitation box="[865,947,1491,1517]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
); apex of endosoma with two spinose processes (
<figureCitation box="[319,436,1526,1553]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Fig. 1J–L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,324,1592,1618]" box="[189,324,1592,1618]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1592,1618]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1592,1618]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[188,1398,1638,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
The specific name is derived frOm the Latin adjective ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[823,965,1638,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteiformis">
<emphasis box="[823,965,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">balteiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the belt-shaped process arising from the ventral margin of the periandrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
