</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1220,412,439]" box="[189,1220,412,439]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length: male 
<quantity box="[611,753,412,439]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="6.3" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="5.9">5.9–6.7 mm</quantity>
(N = 20), female 
<quantity box="[963,1104,412,439]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.45" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="6.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="7.45" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="6.6">6.6–8.3 mm</quantity>
(N = 30).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[188,1401,477,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
COLORATION. General color yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[720,846,477,504]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Eyes blackish brown, ocelli faint yellow, semitranslucent. Antenna, vertex, face and rostrum generally yellowish brown. Pronotum and mesonotum brown. Forewing semi-translucent, costal vein with spots, resembling a U-shape, lateral areas slightly darker; slightly anterior to stigma, posterior to stigma and near fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1019,1046,602,616]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">1+2</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1110,1137,602,616]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">3+4</subScript>
with an irregular puce spot, respectively; apical half of wing with brown patches. Stigma yellowish brown. Veins yellowish brown. Tubercles brown. Hind tibiae yellowish brown. Ventral abdomen blackish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,719,928]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
HEAD AND THORAX. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[520,647,719,745]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.6× as long as wide; lateral carinae strongly elevated, median carina absent. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[449,542,754,780]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) 3.5× as long as wide. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[969,1100,754,780]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.7× as long as vertex; posterior margin forming a right angle. Mesonotum 1.2× as long as pronotum and vertex combined. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[320,448,825,851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1B, E</figureCitation>
) 2.3 × as long as wide, with thirteen apical cells and seven subapical cells; RP with 4 branches; MP with 5 branches (MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[695,711,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">11</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="right" box="[769,786,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">12</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[843,852,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">2</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[910,919,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">3</subScript>
and MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1018,1027,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">4</subScript>
); fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1152,1161,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">1</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1226,1235,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">2</subScript>
basad of fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[231,240,914,928]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">3</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[306,315,914,928]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">4</subScript>
. Metatibiotarsal formula 8/8, second segment of hind tarsus with three platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[187,1399,960,1377]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[506,628,960,987]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1F–G</figureCitation>
) in ventral view symmetrical; in lateral view, lateral lobes arcuate and extended caudally. Medioventral process triangular in ventral view, apical margin pointed. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[303,425,1031,1057]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1F, H</figureCitation>
) flat, tubular, dOrsal margin almOst straight, ventral margin strOngly curved at base in lateral view; asymmetrical, basal right lobe larger than left lobe, 1.6× as long as wide in dorsal view; anal style strap-shaped, not extending beyond anal segment. Gonostyli (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1121,1101,1127]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1G, I</figureCitation>
) symmetrical ventrally; in inner lateral view, dorsal margin concave in middle, apical margin slightly enlarged, bending inwards at an acute angle. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[531,654,1172,1198]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[232,1344,267,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-99@5.[227,1361,259,1847]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862169/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1J–M</figureCitation>
) with five prOcesses. Basal ventral margin Of periandrium with a short spinose process, directed ventrad; left side of ventral margin of periandrium with a belt-shaped process on apical third, apex of process with small teeth. Endosoma broad, generally curved dorsad and cephalad, dorsal margin with multiple small teeth; left side of base with a long spinose process, directed cephalad; apex with two spinose processes, one short and small, directed ventrocephalad, the other slightly longer, directed ventrad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[188,1400,1416,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
FEMALE GENITALIA. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[554,715,1416,1442]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2A–B, D</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized, with a large, nearly quadrate wax plate. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[442,533,1451,1478]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) rectangular, 1.9× as long as wide in dorsal view, anal style linguiform. Gonapophysis VIII (
<figureCitation box="[437,528,1487,1513]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) elongate and slightly curved upwards. Gonapophysis IX (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1330,1487,1513]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) with two middle teeth, distance ratio between middle tooth to apex and length of denticulate portion 2.1. Gonoplac (
<figureCitation box="[319,411,1557,1583]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) rod-like, 4.8× as long as wide in lateral view. Posterior vagina pattern as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[189,283,1592,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,268,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-150@6.[189,1398,265,1394]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Andes balteiformis Wang, Zhi &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♀. A. Genitalia, lateral view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C. Anal segment, dorsal view. D. Tergite IX, caudal view. E. Gonapophysis VIII and gonocoxa VIII, dorsal view. F. Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. G. Gonoplac, inner lateral view. H. Posterior vagina, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
